In the similar way as the interaction of solar wind with Earth’s magnetic field results in the formation of magnetosphere which effectively shields the planet from the solar wind, the possibility that magnetic anomaly regions on Moon can form small-scale magnetospheres (“mini-magnetospheres”) has been suggested from Lunar Prospector observations (Lin et al. 1998). The discovery of “mini-magnetosphere” on Moon was made possible by means of ENA observations from Chandrayaan-1 over the Crisium antipode magnetic anomaly region (Wieser et al. 2010). The spatial extent of the mini-magnetosphere was found to be ∼\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
